# Custom builds for some modules needed to fool LF95 compiler
# in the bad old days so it wouldn't take forever to finish 
# (~14 hours for tree-walker)
# No, Lahey didn't fix their compiler
# (they called the compile times "proper", adding for clarification
# "We don't fix this problem,"
# we worked around their bug by moving USE statements inside procedures
